The Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA) has warned that it will prosecute owners and drivers of heavy duty vehicles involved in accidents that maimed and kill people in the territory. Mr Ikharo Attah, the Chairman, FCTA Ministerial Traffic Management Team, stated this on Wednesday in Nyanya at a rescue operation at two scenes of accidents involving heavy duty vehicles and trucks. He warned that any heavy duty vehicle and truck involved in an accident would be thoroughly investigated. (NAN) 